Two men were arraigned before a Yaba Chief Magistrates’ Court in Lagos for the alleged possession of 90 wraps of Indian hemp. NAN reports that the defendants are Kehinde Kolawole, 30, and Jamiu Surajudeen, 25.They are facing a three-count charge of conspiracy, breach of peace, and indecent act.They, however, pleaded not guilty to the charge. Police prosecutor, SP Thomas Nurudeen, told the court that the defendants committed the offenses at 9pm on Jan. 21, at Abule Ijesha area of Yaba, Lagos. Okorocha Declares For Presidency, Pledges To Surpass Buhari In… First Female Nigeria Police Officer Appointed Adviser For… Nurudeen said residents of the area reported to their local station that some boys were selling different hard drugs in their area. He said a police patrol team was discharged which raided the criminal hideout and arrested the two defendants with a nylon bag containing over 90 sticks of Indian hemp suspected to be for sale.Nurudeen said the offenses contravened the provisions of Sections 168, 134, and 411 of the Criminal Laws of Lagos State, 2015. Chief Magistrate, Peter Nwaka, admitted the defendants to bail in the sum of N50,000 with two sureties in like sum. Nwaka directed that both sureties must reside within the court’s jurisdiction and be gainfully employed with evidence of tax payment to the Lagos State Government. He added that they must have their addresses verified by the court and adjourned the case until Feb. 17 for mention.